# BEAT Platform — Agreed Architecture Decisions

These decisions were made during planning. Follow them; don't re-litigate silently.

## Approach

- Extend the existing Laravel core (orders, payments, commissions, portals).
  Audio/AI work runs in a separate worker path (queue-driven), NOT a full rebuild.

## Subscription lifecycle (status machine)

```
DRAFT → SCRIPT_GENERATING → SCRIPT_READY → PREVIEW_GENERATING → PREVIEW_READY
→ CUSTOMER_APPROVED → AWAITING_PAYMENT → PAYMENT_PENDING → PAID
→ FINAL_AUDIO_GENERATING → READY_FOR_QA → (QA_CHANGES_REQUIRED) → READY_FOR_INSTALLATION
→ EXPORTED → INSTALLATION_IN_PROGRESS → INSTALLED → ACTIVE → EXPIRED
Side states: CANCELLED, FAILED, MANUAL_REVIEW_REQUESTED
```

- Status transitions must be validated (state machine) and audit-logged.
- `starts_at`/`ends_at` set at INSTALLED, not at payment.
- Commission disbursed at INSTALLED, not at PAID.

## AI / Audio pipeline

- Preview BEFORE payment (low quality or watermarked); final HQ audio AFTER payment.
- TTS behind a provider interface (`listVoices` / `generatePreview` / `generateFinal`).
  **Default: self-hosted Meta MMS-TTS** (`facebook/mms-tts-swh`) in `ai-worker/`.
  Azure is optional, not required. Fine-tuned BizTune voices (`local/biztune-*`)
  replace MMS default for commercial production — see `ai-worker/FINETUNE.md`.
  MMS base checkpoint is CC-BY-NC (dev/staging until fine-tuned voices ship).
  Never couple business logic to one vendor.
- AI/audio worker is a separate Python 3.11 service (`ai-worker/`, own Docker
  container). LLM access via OpenAI-compatible adapter (base URL + key + model
  from env) so providers are swappable. Laravel stays the core for orders,
  payments, statuses.
- LLM script generation returns structured JSON (versions, pronunciation_hints,
  estimated_duration, warnings) — server-side validation of duration, business name,
  location, CTA, forbidden claims.
- Audio output specs come from a configurable `AudioOutputProfile` (format, sample
  rate, channels, bit depth, max duration) — never hard-code Vodacom specs.
- Generation limits: 3 script gens, 5 voice previews, 3 music changes, 2 full
  revisions → then manual production ticket (MANUAL_REVIEW_REQUESTED).

## Ops export

- Export is a ZIP batch (manifest.xlsx + final-audio.wav + script.txt + order.json
  + checksum) recorded in an ExportLog (exported_at, exported_by, batch_reference).
  An order must not be exportable into two open batches.

## Media security

- Audio files private; customers get signed, expiring URLs. No public buckets.
